<li id="cite_note-17"><b><a href="#cite_ref-17" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web"><a href="http://blog.wired.com/defense/2007/08/no-pain-ray-for.html" class="external text" title="http://blog.wired.com/defense/2007/08/no-pain-ray-for.html" rel="nofollow">""No Pain Ray for Iraq""</a>. 2007-08-30<span class="printonly">. <a href="http://blog.wired.com/defense/2007/08/no-pain-ray-for.html" class="external free" title="http://blog.wired.com/defense/2007/08/no-pain-ray-for.html" rel="nofollow">http://blog.wired.com/defense/2007/08/no-pain-ray-for.html</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2008-12-13</span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=%22No+Pain+Ray+for+Iraq%22&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft.date=2007-08-30&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fblog.wired.com%2Fdefense%2F2007%2F08%2Fno-pain-ray-for.html&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Active_Denial_System"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
